cs.CR, cs.CY, cs.SI, cs.SE, cs.CC 

Reasoning: 
- cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) is the most likely category as the paper discusses security management within an enterprise. 
- cs.CY (Computers and Society) is also likely as the paper touches on the blurred boundaries between physical and information security, which can have societal implications. 
- cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) and cs.SE (Software Engineering) are possible categories as the paper may discuss the use of software and networks in security management. 
- cs.CC (Computational Complexity) is a less likely category as the paper does not seem to focus on complexity theory.
